objects.name: Pasty Draco
objects.description: Pasty Draco, also known as Gorgon Group, is a threat group consisting of members who are suspected to be Pakistan-based or have other connections to Pakistan. The group has performed a mix of criminal and targeted attacks, including campaigns against government organizations in the United Kingdom, Spain, Russia, and the United States.

objects.name: Campaign 1 - [Playbook] Pasty Draco
objects.description: Starting in February 2018, Palo Alto Networks Unit 42 identified a campaign of attacks performed by members of Pasty Draco targeting governmental organizations in the United Kingdom, Spain, Russia, and the United States. Additionally, during that time, members of Pasty Draco were also performing criminal operations against targets across the globe, often using shared infrastructure with their targeted attack operations.

objects.name: NanoCoreRAT
objects.description: NanocoreRAT is a Trojan that opens a back door and steals information from the compromised computer. It also allows a remote attacker to execute various commands on the infected system. It may achieve persistence on the targeted system by modifying the Registry.
